<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-08-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="379" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-12"><hi rend="italic">August 12,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mora claim definitely settled here by signed agreement to pay one and
                            half million Spanish dollars in gold by 15th proximo in full discharge.
                            This is for your information, not for use with Spanish Government or for
                            other official or public purposes.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Adee</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>